The paper discusses deep learning methods for image recognition, specifically semantic segmentation, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The focus on handling failure modes of deep learning algorithms suggests a connection to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The use of uncertainty quantification techniques and error detection methods suggests a connection to natural language processing (cs.CL) and neural networks (cs.NE) sub-categories.
